The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Briefs
                                                                                                               SPORT BRIEFS
                  
	 Belfast: Fifas rule makers proposed on Saturday to experiment with extra match officials to monitor the penalty box in one of Europes top leagues next season but ditched the idea of a sin-bin for yellow card offenders.    
	Fifa secretary general Jerome Valcke said soccers world governing body had received letters from the French and Italian football associations expressing an interest in putting extra linesmen at each end of the pitch to help alert referees to fouls or diving in their second-tier leagues. We will work until June to decide which league should be used for the experiment for a full season until 2010 with a view to reaching a conclusive decision in 2011, Valcke told reporters.          
	 Bali: Jyoti Randhawa cooked up a sizzling six-under 66 to leapfrog 37 places to tied 9th after the penultimate round of the Enjoy Jakarta Indonesia Open Golf tournament here Saturday. Digvijay Singh carded one-under 71 to be tied 13th, two strokes ahead of senior pro Gaurav Ghei (74). Gaganjeet Bhullars second successive 71 had him tied 45th while S.S.P. Chowrasia was tied 65th.          
	Playa del Carmen (Mexico): Arjun Atwal returned an improved card of two-over 72 in the second round but that was not enough for the Orlando-based golfer to make the cut at the Mayakoba Golf Classic here.        
	New Delhi: Chetan Anands loss to Chinas Weijie Gong meant it was curtains for India at the Yonex German Open Grand Prix badminton tournament Friday. Chetan lost 21-19, 19-21, 12-21.The pair of Jwala Gutta and D. Viju lost to the Chinese duo of Bo Zheng and Jin Ma 17-21, 12-21.          
	Dubai: Novak Djokovic defeated fourth seed David Ferrer 7-5, 6-3 on Saturday to win the Dubai Championships. It was the top-seeded Serbians 12th title.          
	Mumbai: Karan Mehta and Trishala Menkar clinched the boys and girls under-12 titles respectively in the All-India Talent Series tennis tournament for the Premjit Lall Trophy here on Saturday. Mehta prevailed over second seed Aryan Goveas 6-2, 6-2 in the boys final while Trishala overcame third seed Mahrukh Kokni 6-2, 6-3.        
	New Delhi: Rohan Bopanna and Jarrko Nieminen crashed out of the $500,000 Delray Beach International after losing their quarter final match 6-4, 3-6, 8-10 to fourth seeds Eric Butorac and Bruno Soares.          
	Lahore: The World Anti-Doping Agency (Wada) on Saturday endorsed a one-year ban on Pakistans Mohammed Asif, saying it will not appeal against his punishment.                                                                                                                                                                       
